AIRA Chatbot (Angular 13 + OpenAI GPTn4) HighnLevel Design (HLD) & LownLevel Design (LLD) AIRA is an AI-powered chatbot embedded in an Angular 13 web application. It uses OpenAI GPTn4 for conversational intelligence and a document-aware retrieval layer to ground answers in product manuals, release notes, and help docs. This document describes the high-level architecture, component interactions, and a detailed low-level design to implement AIRA entirely from the frontend (direct OpenAI calls using an API key), plus a minimal viable document-ingestion pipeline. HighnLevel Design (HLD) Architecture Overview • Angular Frontend: Floating chat launcher, chat popup, message list, input box, feedback controls, and state management. • OpenAI GPTn4: Chat completions API called directly from the browser over HTTPS with Bearer API key. • Document Knowledge Base: Preprocessed chunks of product docs with text embeddings for semantic retrieval (MVP: innmemory index; Scale: external vector DB). • Feedback Collection: Thumbsnup/down + optional comment routed to a feedback endpoint or analytics for continuous improvement. Core Flow • User opens chat → types a question. • Frontend retrieves topnK relevant doc chunks via semantic similarity (query embedding vs. stored embeddings). • Frontend composes GPTn4 request: system prompt + (optional) recent chat history + retrieved doc snippets + user query. • OpenAI returns an answer → UI renders text, sources (links), and image previews (if any). • User gives feedback (n/n + optional comment) → sent to feedback service. Document Context Options MVP: InnMemory Embeddings — Precompute embeddings for doc chunks; ship as JSON with the app; compute cosine similarity in the browser. Simple, zero infra, good for small corpora. Scaled: Vector Database — Store embeddings + metadata in Pinecone/Weaviate/Qdrant/Chroma; query topnK via API. Fast, scalable, centralized KB. Document Ingestion Pipeline (Minimal Viable) • Upload: Admin provides PDFs/DOCX/HTML/MD. • Extract: Convert to raw text; keep headings/sections. • Chunk: Split into ~300–800 token chunks with overlap. • Embed: Generate vectors using OpenAI embeddings or SentenceTransformers. • Index: Store as JSON (MVP) or upsert to a vector DB (scaled). • Verify: Sanityncheck counts/dimensions; run a sample query. State & Security Chat state is clientnside (service or component). Consider local/session storage to persist across refresh. API key is used from the frontend (environment config) and sent over HTTPS; for production hardening, prefer a thin proxy to conceal the key. LownLevel Design (LLD) Angular Components • ChatLauncherComponent: Floating icon; toggles chat window visibility; persists open/closed state. • ChatWindowComponent: Header (title, expand/minimize/close), message list (user/assistant bubbles), input box (send on Enter/Click), typing indicator, error banners. • ChatMessageComponent: Renders message bubble; assistant bubbles show source links, optional image previews, and feedback controls (n/n). • FeedbackInlineComponent: Textarea shown on n; submit sends comment then shows a thanknyou. Services • ChatService: Builds OpenAI request (system prompt + history + doc snippets + user query); POST /v1/chat/completions; parses response; handles errors; optional streaming. • DocumentService: Loads embedding index (MVP from assets/doc_index.json) or queries vector DB; computes query embedding; returns topnK chunks with metadata (source title/URL/page, optional image refs). • FeedbackService: Sends rating and optional

comment to a feedback endpoint or logs to analytics. • ConversationService (optional): Holds messages across routes; offers add/clear APIs; supports summarization/truncation when token budget is tight. Request Composition (to GPTn4) • System message: AIRA persona & guardrails (cite docs, be concise, say “don’t know” when unsure). • Context: Concatenate topnK doc snippets with source labels; keep total tokens within model limits. • History: Last N turns (or tokenncapped) to preserve continuity. • User message: The latest question verbatim. • Params: model=gptn4, temperature≈0.3–0.7, max_tokens per UI need; enable streaming later if desired. Similarity Search (MVP) • Compute query embedding via OpenAI embeddings API. • Cosine similarity over preloaded vectors (NumPynlike math in TS or a small helper). • Pick topnK (e.g., 3–5); dedupe highly similar chunks; maintain source diversity if possible. • Map chunk metadata → hyperlinks (e.g., /assets/docs/Manual.pdf#page=45) and optional image URLs. UI/UX Details • Typing indicator while awaiting response; replace with answer on success; show error banner on failure. • Input disabled during request to avoid overlapping calls (or queue). • Links open in a new tab; images constrained to chat width; accessible labels on controls. • Expand/minimize persists across routes; optional ‘Clear chat’ to reset state. Error & RatenLimit Handling Graceful errors (‘Something went wrong, please retry’), exponential backoff for transient failures, basic debouncing on send, and optional pernsession rate limits. Security Notes • Use HTTPS; never log API keys; restrict key with org/project limits. • Frontend key is inherently exposable — for production, prefer a minimal proxy to sign requests. • Only send nonnsensitive doc text to OpenAI; exclude confidential content from the KB or mask/redact. Minimal Ingestion Script Outline 1) Extract text → 2) chunk_text() → 3) embed_chunks() → 4) write assets/doc_index.json doc_index.json item schema: { "id": "UserManual#p45_c2", "text": "Hold reset button 10s until LED flashes...", "embedding": [ ... ], "source": {"title": "User Manual", "url": "/assets/docs/UserManual.pdf#page=45", "page": 45}, "media": [{"type": "image", "url": "/assets/images/reset_diagram.png"}] }
